a, (ii) shortening of the interval where degree of swelling Q adopts its maximum value, and (iii) a weak increase in the maximum degree of swelling. We proceed with the analysis of swelling of a cationic PE gel with r1 = 3.4 Â· 102 (the same value as in Fig. 11), S+ = 5.0 Â· 102
